I said last monday was the day from hell.&nbsp; and also prefaced it with sort of.&nbsp; because it wasn't that bad.&nbsp; little things were just irritating the hell out of me.

word of warning.&nbsp; this writing is going to be choppy and horrible.&nbsp; I apologize in advance, usually I'm not this bad.

today was a day from hell.&nbsp; they called me at 9:30-9:45.&nbsp; I said I would be there 10:30 or 11:00.&nbsp; my mom wanted me to do stuff, and plus I haven't had a day off from there in over a week.&nbsp; I got there a little after 11.&nbsp; they had already done a few cases, and we probably had about 45 cases of shoes to go .&nbsp; 22 from redwing alone.&nbsp; so, ok.&nbsp; it was pretty steady, not crazy busy.&nbsp; but matt just got back from an industrial run, and then adrian said, we got the green light for trenton.&nbsp; and I almost said, "oh no.&nbsp; we have at least 30 cases back there, and you, you lazy piece of shit, aren't going anywhere."&nbsp; but I didn't.&nbsp; because I'm not a manager, and it wouldn't have made a difference.&nbsp; since, he probably would have just pouted and not done a goddamn thing anyway. 

alison left at like 1:30 or 2, which was fine because she's got that heart thing.&nbsp; it got busy.&nbsp; I was checking off shoes box by box, checking specials, and trying to help customers.&nbsp; this other chick (I call her box of rocks), janine, isn't doing much.&nbsp; I mean she tries, but she is really dumb as a box of rocks.&nbsp; she tries, but she is practically worthless.&nbsp; esp. when it's a) busy and/or b) we get hit with a big shipment of shoes.&nbsp; you know what she was doing when I was doing all this?&nbsp; calling fucking specials to let them know they were here.&nbsp; I'm sorry, but that can wait until we are done with all the shipments.&nbsp; just because you can't handle two things at once, I'm stuck basically by myself putting away&nbsp; a lot of shoes, helping customers, etc.&nbsp; NOT fun.&nbsp; I went up front to handle a question from alex (she said, if you guys are busy, I'll come back there.&nbsp; I said, no, I could use a break. she laughed).&nbsp; I thought I was going to kill janine today.&nbsp; so, I went up there and they figured it was her mistake.&nbsp; it usually is,&nbsp; but it wasn't.&nbsp; so, I called the guy and etc.&nbsp; I get off the phone, and say "I don't know what to do with this.&nbsp; chuck it for all I care at this point."&nbsp; we are talking about some other stuff, and I put my head in my hand and say, I guess I should go check on box of rocks."&nbsp; alex is like, "you are probably should."&nbsp; I walk back, and the box I was working on, which all she had to do was put away.&nbsp; she didn't touch 1 fucking box.&nbsp; there was 1 person back there.&nbsp; it was just aggravating.&nbsp; beyond belief.&nbsp; 

janine called travis and tom to see if either or both of them could work.&nbsp; travis came around 4, and tom around 5.&nbsp; thank god travis showed up when he did.&nbsp; since around 12:30 that afternoon until 4 we had done around 8 boxes of redwing.&nbsp; that is not a good ratio.&nbsp; so, I had eric (another part-timer) grab some more and put them on the floor.&nbsp; to be sorted, etc.&nbsp; matt came back at like 4:20.&nbsp; and he actually worked.&nbsp; probably sensed that I was so not in the mood to fuck around.&nbsp; either way, we got all the shoes done by 5.&nbsp; I went and got food for me and a few other people.&nbsp; I seriously needed to get out of there.&nbsp; I got a cheesesteak, and a little eclair (sp rach?) for me.&nbsp; the eclair was perfectly chocolate, custardy goodness.&nbsp; I was in a much better mood after I got help, and even more so after I got food.&nbsp; after that, all was fine.&nbsp; 

I know I bitch sometimes, but that place is just beyond illogical and seriously inefficient beyond belief.&nbsp; I need a real job.&nbsp; like now.&nbsp; yay for vodka.&nbsp; thank russians for vodka.&nbsp; 

that is all.&nbsp; thanks for reading about my boring life.&nbsp; venting is good.&nbsp; venting is very good.&nbsp;

this one was good, not great but not bad either.&nbsp; Why does that actress (azura skye I think) always play something to do with death (she was in a few buffy episodes, all related to death)?&nbsp; and there was an xf reference too (the mold poison) with the guy who killed the chick above him and almost killed scully.&nbsp; I know, I'm such a dork.&nbsp; anyway, loved the cam/house scenes!&nbsp; they were hot.&nbsp; 

woo for the black mormon guy decking house.&nbsp; I'm rooting for #13, past that I hope the cutthroat bitch doesn't get it.&nbsp; fucking with her about the guy she killed is just not kosher for human beings, but house of course loved it.&nbsp; the collar was over the top though.&nbsp; .&nbsp; but I doubt they would have two chicks get it.&nbsp; esp. if there's only two slots, now.&nbsp; I'm not too big on the surgeon either, he's way too hands off and precocious.&nbsp; "I'm not digging.&nbsp; if something happens to these hands..."&nbsp; poor bosley, though.&nbsp; he was the man, but it made sense for him to go.&nbsp; he is too much like house, but without the degree.&nbsp; woo for the banter with the preppy surgeon guy, "Oh, I guess they didn't teach that at your medical school."&nbsp; shazam!

boo for there definitely not being enough wilson, what was it one scene?&nbsp; maybe a few more, but not much more than that.&nbsp; I feel kinda bad for foreman, though.&nbsp; House-lite--&gt;lol.&nbsp; cuddy:&nbsp; I will give you none of those...you are house-lite.&nbsp; the only person who will hire you now is the person who hired house-classic.&nbsp; take that foreman, you should have taken the offer and run.&nbsp; that means only two open slots, right?&nbsp; or does he not count?&nbsp; and is he kind of stuck there forever?&nbsp; a never ending blacklisted dude?&nbsp; that would suck hairy syphillic monkey balls. one thing is for sure there will be non-stop ribbing from chase to foreman.&nbsp; can't blame the guy either.&nbsp; 4man was constantly doing it to chase, and paybacks are a bitch.&nbsp; wonder what cameron will do?&nbsp; it's an interesting turn of events.&nbsp; but I'm still sad to see bosley go.&nbsp; 

that's it, 
lex

this will be a very brief review...I is tired.&nbsp; I worked 12 hours today, but it's a good tired.&nbsp; like I did something today tired.&nbsp; still fucking tired, though.&nbsp; yay for oily monitoring wells (semi-sarcastic, because it can be a lot of fun.&nbsp; but three of them is a lot to purge...)

ok...back to the review.&nbsp; I liked this one.&nbsp; I loved that he hired #13 (woo!), and that he wanted to experience death so he electrocuted himself.&nbsp; and I hate to tell that you that I was right at the end was freaking brilliant.&nbsp; "because you guys are idiots, and I want to bump off the other girls."&nbsp; I liked it because it made him seem like a human being (much like one day one room, which I know a lot of you didn't like, but whatever).&nbsp; I hate the fact that I'm using "I liked" over and over again, very unlike me.&nbsp; but my brain is pretty much mush right now.&nbsp; so I'm sorry about that.&nbsp; 

I HATED that the dog died.&nbsp; that was NOT cool.&nbsp; I thought it was over grief.&nbsp; but still cool that he hired the girl because he realized that she'd never do it again.&nbsp; poor guy, though.&nbsp; 

foreman fired, really didn't see that coming.&nbsp; wonder where that story line is going.&nbsp; 

ok,
that was probably really incoherent (much more so than my drunken one).&nbsp; but there it is.&nbsp; I go bed. 

-lex

ok, WTF.&nbsp; he fired #23 (aka the chick from the er, or Kathy Adams) within the first 2 minutes.&nbsp; all sorts of not spiffy...it sucks hairy monkey balls.&nbsp; I liked the old dude, though.&nbsp; he was cool.&nbsp; 

not spiffy was cam with blonde hair....so not liking that.&nbsp; loved that he asked the plastic surgeon if he saw a blond guy with peach fuzz.&nbsp; 

not enough wilson, but the arizona thing was a nice touch.&nbsp; 

YAY cammy's back (probably a limited time, but still, YAY).&nbsp; big time eye sex with house in the last scene.&nbsp; woo.&nbsp; even if she was smug, still major eye sex.

the religion quote was my favorite:&nbsp; " most religious people don't listen to reasonable arguments.&nbsp; then there would be no religious people"&nbsp; best quote I've heard in awhile.

hehe.

overall, pretty good epi.&nbsp; I knew something was fishy when wilson said they were in AZ, but the calling cam was the icing.&nbsp; woo.

ok...I like the chick with the camisole thing who was washing the car (and pretended to quit, I have no idea what number she is), 6/9 (that was awesome.&nbsp; "I approve of your shamelessness, but you are still fired." until you mentioned getting wasted on tequila...woo!).&nbsp; eh on 13 she's so in your face.&nbsp; you can't have two in-your-face people...it's just not a good dynamic, and not sure of the other numbers.&nbsp; 39 might be there b/c of the boob job, but kinda iffy on him personally.&nbsp; so house will probably love him.&nbsp; and loved the old guy, as I mentioned.&nbsp; I liked #10 until he narced on the chick, he was SO fired after that.&nbsp; what do you guys think of the muslim dude?&nbsp; is he gone?&nbsp; too many numbers after a long day...couldn't quite keep them all straight *hangs head in shame*

love psych wilson.&nbsp; 

-lex :-)&nbsp;

ok, I think I pulled a hamstring or something else in my thigh yesterday at work (doing something I've literally done hundreds of times).&nbsp; I put heat on it yesterday and again tonight, but it still tightens up after sitting for longer period of time (yay for recliners).&nbsp; anyone have any suggestions?&nbsp; at least it's not like a constant pain, it's more of a dull ache after sitting.&nbsp; I'm going to stretch it again, and *makes mental note* not to overdue it at the gym, and THEN go to work without stretching said muscle ever again*&nbsp; 

on the other hand, the past couple of days I've gotten really nice compliments at work from customers.&nbsp; like telling my boss I should get a raise (three people have said that to my boss the last week or so).&nbsp; it makes everything worth it (maybe, even cheerleading moms...nah they are still the worst ever).&nbsp; so that's always all sorts of spiffy, even though he drives me crazy sometimes.&nbsp; 

-lex :-)

I don't know whether you guys have heard about this.&nbsp; But some fucker got on TWO trans-Atlantic flights with a highly drug-resistant form of TB.&nbsp; TB is a highly contagious, deadly disease that is making a terrifying comeback.&nbsp; And this fucker KNEW he had it, was told not to fly (twice), and decided to risk who knows how many people's lives.&nbsp; I hope he dies a slow, horrible, painful death.&nbsp; he's more info on it:&nbsp; http://abclocal.go.com/wpvi/story?section=healthcheck&amp;id=5337103

I hate people.&nbsp; 

-lex
